	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ah, the infamous Ogre Camp in West Karana. No one really knows much about these guys. The guards con &quot;amiable&quot; to everyone, but the shamans, shamanesses, priestesses, and Chief Goonda are all &quot;threateningly&quot;. These guys/gals are KOS to everyone, and drop the infamous Bone Armor! Rather, the guards are just that, useless guards, level 19-21. Chief Goonda drops Batskull Earrings (+5 int) and I hear a Sheer Bone Mask (+4 int, some AC) He's a level 35 or so shaman. (Some say he's only level 29, but since when could shamans summon pets at 29?) The shamans are also like the guards, not much loot on them other than the odd weapon and such. Got a Batfang Headband off one once, though. Something like +3 wisdom. The shamanesses are good bets, with their common drop being Giant Snakespine Belts (+5 agility, +5 sv poison, 4 AC) and rare being the Chipped Bone Bracer (Not sure about these... something like +3 or 4 wis, I think, looks like chain) The priestesses drop the &quot;real&quot; bone, common drop being bone armplates (look like chain, I think 4 AC, +4 agility, -4 dexterity) and the rare is bone legplates (look like chain, something similar to the armplates) Factions lower with the Greenbloods and a few other Ogreish guilds for killing them, nothing big. Hope that clears up all about the Ogres of West Karana. Apologies for messing up what drop what. (Only camped them a few times)<BR>
Munkey.
				</font>
			</td>

