				Zen,<BR>
<BR>
I don't think this is a Grobb quest at all, or even one for us evil races.  I think Dorn's note is part of an Oggok shaman quest (please check threads on Marda's Quests A'Plenty, Marda's Secrit Quests in Oggok, and Chief Goonda Quest in WK).  It is within these quests that we learn about Zimbittle and Dorn's 'Password'.  The last stage of Marda's quest appears to be handing in Zimbittle's pouch in exchange for 2 lvl 1 shaman spells, which makes no sense to me as killing troll Bashers for the necklaces requires a lvl 35+ character.  <BR>
<BR>
IMO an ogre shaman with REALLY good faction with Marda needs to hand in Zimbittle's pouch a few times and see if she gives anything out as a rare.  If not, perhaps handing Marda the pouch triggers an event in the Ogre Camp out in WK.  <BR>
<BR>
Dorn's note and Chief Goonda in WK both refer to a 'Crystal Shard', maybe relates to the 'Crystal Shard' referred to in recent GM events.  Anyway, I think the Crystal Shard is the general direction that this quest is headed.  <BR>
<BR>
It may yet turn out that this is in fact an evil quest, and we need to track down and kill this 'agent' dispatched by Marda to retrieve the Shard.  <BR>
<BR>
If anyone has any further information on Goonda's quest, Marda's quest, or the triggering of any unusual events in the WK ogre camp, I'm all ears.  This Crystal Shard has me interested.<BR>

